{"questionId":"ad300285-6ff9-46a9-97ab-7356c9cd2965_22","correctAnswer":"B","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Find the vertex x-coordinate using \\(x = -b/(2a)\\)","content":"$r(t) = -2t^{2} + 55t$, so $a = -2$, $b = 55$. Vertex at:<br/>$$t^{*} = -\\frac{b}{2a} = -\\frac{55}{2(-2)} = \\frac{55}{4}.$$"},{"title":"Compute the maximum of r(t)","content":"$$r\\!\\left(\\tfrac{55}{4}\\right) = 55 \\cdot \\tfrac{55}{4} - 2\\left(\\tfrac{55}{4}\\right)^{2} = \\tfrac{55^{2}}{4} - \\tfrac{2 \\cdot 55^{2}}{16} = 2\\left(\\tfrac{55}{4}\\right)^{2}.$$"},{"title":"Maximum of s(t) = r(t) + 1","content":"$$s_{\\max} = 1 + 2\\left(\\frac{55}{4}\\right)^{2}.$$<br/>That matches choice B — <strong>B</strong> is correct.","desmosExpressions":["r(t) = 55t - 2t^{2}","s(t) = 55t - 2t^{2} + 1","(13.75, 379.125)"]}]}